  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically includes:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Components\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of large/suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Financial institution compliance obligations\n- Penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial regulators\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Specialized anti-money laundering units\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Employee training\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping protocols\n\n7. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial fines\n- License revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
